      passage: `<p>Liverpool Football Club took more than half of the home matches it played between 1947 and 2003, part of what has long marked it as a leading British professional soccer club. On top of that, Liverpool&mdash;whose home kit is mainly red&mdash;did better at home than Watford Football Club, whose home kit is not red. Research has shown that a great many people link the color red with power and dominance. Earlier experiences with red objects like stop signs can even make people react to the color red warily and with hesitation. If these findings hold in the setting of athletic competition, they might suggest that, in matches at Liverpool&rsquo;s home ground, opponents may have ______</p>`,
