      passage: `<p>Writers like Laura Esquivel helped fuel the surge of Mexican literature in the years after the Mexican Revolution (1910&ndash;1920). Works from that era make up an ______ share of what is taken to be the Mexican literary canon, yet nineteenth-century figures like Justo Sierra O&rsquo;Reilly deserve to be seen as just as central to it.</p>`,
