      passage: `<p>In the late 1970s, the prices of collectible stamps printed decades earlier climbed sharply, which had the counterintuitive result of ______ demand: buyers who had shown no prior interest in old stamps suddenly crowded the market, convinced that prices would keep climbing and that the stamps could later be resold at a profit.</p>`,
